## Spec (SRS.md:191-209)
FR-21: Grounding Checks L5 — Semantic Alignment Verification
- Priority P1
- Validate cosine similarity between LLM output and knowledge source embeddings
- Default threshold=0.75, configurable via constructor
- GroundingChecker.check(llm_output, source_texts) → GroundingResult(grounded, score, reason, best_match_index)
- Empty source_texts → grounded=False, reason=\"no_source\"
- Steps: embed LLM output → embed sources → cosine similarity → max score → threshold compare
- Grounding failure → LLM output discarded, route to Layer 4 (escalation)

## Architecture (SAD.md:311-332)
- GroundingResult: frozen dataclass with grounded: bool, score: float, reason: str, best_match_index: int
- Default model: paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM-L12-v2 (384-dim)
- Embedding function injectable via constructor
- Default threshold=0.75

## Implementation (grounding.py): GroundingResult frozen dataclass, GroundingChecker with check() method, _cosine_similarity function, _default_embedding_fn lazy-load

## Tests (test_fr21.py): 17 tests all pass, 90% coverage. Mock embeddings for deterministic cosine values.","phase":3,"date":"2026-05-17"}
